{
  "stem": "19923.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 99.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They didn't get out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they stayed behind in Germany-- in-- in Brussels.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And in 1943, they had to go into hiding because the Germans were rounding up all the Jews from Brussels.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There were 25,000 Jews that were rounded up from Belgium.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And my mother evidently being in hiding in the attic got stir crazy.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And as my cousins tell me, she thought she could pass by for a Belgian.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And she left my two sisters in the attic and went into the street and was picked up.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the last one to saw her was my first cousin in Belgium, my mother's older sister's son, Joe Kirchenstein, K-I-R-C-H-E-N-S-T-E-I-N, who also survived the war.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He had been picked up by the Germans and he was taken to a collecting point in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "From there, they went-- from there, they were shipped to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He's the last one that saw my mother there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It's called Maligne, M-A-L-I-G-N-E, where he was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And he talked to my mother on the other side of the fence.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he even knew what transport she went and when she was taken by transport directly to Auschwitz and immediately gassed and cremated on August 1st, 1943.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The same day they arrived, she was cremated.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "The reason I know that is because the people that were made into slave laborers, they put a tattoo on them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "If they didn't get the tattoo, that meant you went right to the gas chamber and that's how she perished.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My sisters, immediately when that happened, they put them in-- they were able to place them in a Catholic home, in a convent.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were hid by the-- the nuns in a Catholic convent for the rest of the war.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
